WEBVTT

00:18.852 --> 00:20.321
BRIA:
We're not safe

00:20.421 --> 00:22.523
and that's why
I need your help.

00:22.623 --> 00:26.660
And that's why I need us
to move in with you, okay?

00:26.760 --> 00:28.929
DONALD:
Follow Mr. Paulson home,
make sure he's all right.

00:29.029 --> 00:31.565
Ye-yes, I'd like to
report a accident.

00:31.665 --> 00:33.101
IAN:
You're here because
the trial's happening

00:33.201 --> 00:34.568
and you are a key witness.

00:34.668 --> 00:37.138
Like, you are not innocent,
not by a fucking long shot.

00:37.238 --> 00:38.972
Do not try to fucking play me.

00:39.073 --> 00:41.142
That's a bug, man.
That's a fucking bug.

00:41.242 --> 00:42.943
KAYLA:
Who put this here?

00:43.043 --> 00:44.178
BRIA:
We don't feel safe.

00:44.278 --> 00:45.646
This was the best place
for us to come.

00:45.746 --> 00:47.281
- Please.
- Nobody is calling the cops.

00:47.381 --> 00:49.350
DIANE:
We're calling the cops.

00:49.450 --> 00:51.319
BRIA:
You better call the cops, Paul!

00:51.419 --> 00:54.288
*

01:05.633 --> 01:08.502
[ siren blaring ]

01:19.713 --> 01:20.781
COP #1:
Put your hands in the air!

01:23.284 --> 01:24.885
Put your hands in the air!

01:24.985 --> 01:27.288
[ indistinct shouting ]

01:27.388 --> 01:29.257
COP #2:
Get your hands up!

01:29.357 --> 01:30.658
COP #1:
Put your weapon down!

01:33.127 --> 01:35.028
Do you have
any more weapons on you?

01:35.129 --> 01:37.298
- I need a verbal no.
- No.

01:37.398 --> 01:38.866
On the ground. Now!

01:40.534 --> 01:42.170
Face down!

01:45.573 --> 01:46.674
Don't move!

01:47.908 --> 01:48.909
Don't move!

01:49.009 --> 01:50.778
[ indistinct chatter ]

01:54.081 --> 01:55.316
You have the right
to remain silent.

01:55.416 --> 01:56.917
Anything you say can be

01:57.017 --> 01:58.619
used against you
in a court of law.

01:58.719 --> 01:59.687
You have the right
to an attorney.

01:59.787 --> 02:02.323
- That's my daughter.
- Excuse me, ma'am?

02:02.423 --> 02:04.192
BRIA:
That's my daughter,
she didn't do anything.

02:04.292 --> 02:06.194
She should come with me.
Did you hear what I said?

02:06.294 --> 02:08.762
That's my daughter.
She should come with me.

02:08.862 --> 02:10.130
COP #1:
You don't get to make
the calls now, ma'am.

02:10.231 --> 02:12.366
KAYLA:
Get off of me!

02:12.466 --> 02:13.667
Fuck off!

02:13.767 --> 02:15.769
Get off!

02:15.869 --> 02:17.305
- Get off of me!
- She's a kid.

02:17.405 --> 02:19.072
- That's my daughter!
- Stop it! Get away!

02:19.173 --> 02:21.575
Are you listening to
what I'm saying to you?

02:21.675 --> 02:23.177
IAN:
I'm Marshal Ian Olsen.

02:23.277 --> 02:25.112
I'm gonna need you to release
her into my custody.

02:25.213 --> 02:26.947
COP #1:
We can't do that, sir.
She fired a gun.

02:27.047 --> 02:28.816
- Residents say she was tres--
- Yeah, I wanna go with you.

02:28.916 --> 02:30.651
We've got to process her before
we can release her to you.

02:30.751 --> 02:32.286
Even then, we will need
a court order.

02:32.386 --> 02:34.121
- I don't wanna go with him.
- I need her to come with me.

02:34.222 --> 02:35.889
- This is above you.
- I don't wanna go with him.

02:35.989 --> 02:37.291
I wanna go to the station.

02:37.391 --> 02:38.626
IAN:
Well, she's obviously
not thinking straight.

02:38.726 --> 02:40.861
Can you just keep her in the car
while I do my due diligence?

02:40.961 --> 02:42.330
Please listen to what I'm
saying. I wanna go with you.

02:42.430 --> 02:43.597
We need to call it in before
I can release her to you.

02:43.697 --> 02:45.233
- I don't wanna go with him.
- By all means. Thanks, man.

02:45.333 --> 02:46.800
Please listen to what
I'm saying, I wanna go

02:46.900 --> 02:48.202
to the station with you.
Please.

02:48.302 --> 02:50.238
I don't need to go
with him, okay?

02:52.340 --> 02:53.807
KAYLA:
Bria.

02:53.907 --> 02:56.644
Bria! Look at me!
Look at me!

02:56.744 --> 02:58.779
- Bria!
- It's gonna be okay, Kayla.

03:00.248 --> 03:01.915
I promise.
You're safe now.

03:03.584 --> 03:04.818
We're safe.

03:05.753 --> 03:06.720
It's gonna be okay.

03:11.992 --> 03:14.795
[ indistinct chatter on radio ]

03:17.998 --> 03:20.634
MAN ON RADIO:
'B as in Bravo,
R as in Romeo'

03:20.734 --> 03:23.837
'I as in India,
A as in Alfa.'

03:23.937 --> 03:26.507
[ indistinct chatter on radio ]

03:33.847 --> 03:36.617
COP #1:
You're all clear, sir.
Sorry about that.

03:36.717 --> 03:39.453
IAN:
It's no problem.
Just doing your job.

03:39.553 --> 03:41.289
- Have a good night, sir.
- Good night, officer.

03:45.793 --> 03:49.196
No, don't go, Bria!
You can't leave me! Bria!

03:49.297 --> 03:51.465
- Sh-she gonna be safe?
- Since when do you care?

03:51.565 --> 03:54.368
I do care. Is-is she gonna be
safe, I just wanna know.

03:54.468 --> 03:55.903
Yeah, so you can cash in.

04:04.578 --> 04:06.647
IAN:
Yes, sir. Yes, sir,
I realize that, sir.

04:07.848 --> 04:09.283
I made the call myself.

04:11.885 --> 04:12.853
Yes, sir. I'm sorry.

04:14.422 --> 04:16.223
I had to make
a split-second decision

04:16.324 --> 04:18.025
and I didn't mean
to go over your head.

04:18.125 --> 04:19.660
With the trial date so close

04:19.760 --> 04:21.495
I just didn't want
any complications.

04:23.163 --> 04:25.666
Yes, sir. I understand.

04:25.766 --> 04:27.768
I was worried she'd try to
squirm out of testifying, sir.

04:29.670 --> 04:30.604
Yes, sir.

04:32.005 --> 04:33.441
I understand, sir,
it won't happen again.

04:35.175 --> 04:37.878
*

04:44.217 --> 04:45.419
[ car door slams ]

04:50.791 --> 04:52.693
Get out.

04:52.793 --> 04:53.827
Get the fuck out.

05:00.434 --> 05:01.802
You like this place, huh?

05:04.304 --> 05:05.939
Seems nice.

05:06.039 --> 05:08.376
I, I-I don't know what you mean.

05:08.476 --> 05:09.577
Is this
where you bring the men

05:09.677 --> 05:10.911
you whore yourself out to
for money?

05:16.417 --> 05:18.619
Are you mad
because I had a boyfriend?

05:18.719 --> 05:20.454
IAN:
A boyfriend?
That's what you call it?

05:22.856 --> 05:24.392
There were more.
How-how many more were there?

05:24.492 --> 05:26.494
- I know at least one.
- I don't--

05:26.594 --> 05:28.596
Actually, shut up.
Shut up.

05:28.696 --> 05:30.297
I don't wanna hear another
fucking lie out of your mouth.

05:30.398 --> 05:31.365
I don't want to hear you
manipulate your words

05:31.465 --> 05:32.900
about who you fucked.

05:33.000 --> 05:34.001
Who you fucked for money.

05:36.704 --> 05:38.305
He paid for your company.

05:38.406 --> 05:40.340
You're paid to accompany me.

05:40.441 --> 05:43.210
That's my fucking job.

05:43.310 --> 05:46.013
I have let you off the hook
so many times

05:46.113 --> 05:48.081
and you violated
every fucking rule

05:48.181 --> 05:50.183
